<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    {{! Document Settings }}
    <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html" charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge,chrome=1" /> {{! Page Meta }}
    <title>{{#if title}}{{title}} | {{/if}} Japanese Tool</title>
    <meta name="description" content="{{meta_description}}" />

    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta name="HandheldFriendly" content="True">
    <meta name="MobileOptimized" content="320">
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/css/style.css" />
</head>

<body>
    <header class="container index-header">
        <img class="logo" src="/img/logo.jpg" alt="Japanese Tools"/>
    </header>
    {{! Everything else gets inserted here }}
    {{{body}}}

    <!-- About / Modal -->
    <div id="aboutIcon">
        <a href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#kanjiAboutModal">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>
        </a>
    </div>
    <div class="modal fade" id="kanjiAboutModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="kanjiAboutModalLabel">
        <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
            <div class="modal-content">
                <div class="modal-header">
                    <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
                    <img alt="Japanese Tools" src="/img/logo.jpg" class="logo"/>
                </div>
                <div class="modal-body">
                    <p>Japanese Tools currently has one tool designed for looking up and producing stroke orders.</p>
                    <h4>Copyright</h4>
                    <p>Kanji Tool site design and coding Copyright 2016 Kyle Wagner.</p>
                    <p>The backend is built on the <a href="http://expressjs.com/">Express</a> for <a href="https://nodejs.org">Node.js</a> with <a href="https://jquery.com/">jQuery</a> and <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/">Bootstrap</a> for the frontend.
                    <h4>Source Code</h4>
                    <a href="https://github.com/wazts/japanese-tools">Japanese Tools</a> @ <a href="https://github.com">Github</a>
                    <h4>Attributions</h4>
                    <p>The Kanji Tool uses the following open source projects and APIs for the kanji data.
                    <table class="table">
                        <tr>
                            <td>
                                <a href="http://kanjivg.tagaini.net/">KanjiVG</a>
                            </td>
                            <td>
                                Kanji stroke order diagrams
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>
                                <a href="https://wanikani.com">WaniKani API</a>
                            </td>
                            <td>
                                The WaniKani Public API is provided for free by <a href="https://tofugu.com">Tofugu LLC</a>.
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="/js/app.js"></script>

</body>
</html>
